for aws:
1.static website

a.create ec2 instance - ssh and http allow 
b.ubuntu terminal (where pem file exist)- 
chmod 400 file.pem
ls -l file.pem 

if error: cp file.pem ~/
          cd ~ 
          then run b 
c. ssh -i ~/file.pem ubuntu@public_ip
d. sudo apt update
e. sudo apt install apache2 -y
f.sudo systemctl start apache2
sudo systemctl enable apache2
g. sudo nano /var/www/html/index.html
then add code
Press Ctrl + O
Press Enter
Press Ctrl + X
h. cat /var/www/html/index.html    --> if you want to show the code on terminal
f. browser : http://public-ip

2.file sharing 

a.create 2 instances(sender and receiver) - ssh allow
b.ubuntu terminal (where pem file exist)- 
chmod 400 file.pem
ls -l file.pem 

if error: cp file.pem ~/
          cd ~ 
          then run b 
c. scp -i ~/file.pem ~/file.pem ubuntu@sender_public_ip:~
d. ssh -i ~/file.pem ubuntu@ sender_public_ip
e. chmod 400 file.pem
f. echo "This file was securely transferred between AWS instances" > sample.txt
g.cat sample.txt
h.scp -i ~/file.pem sample.txt ubuntu@receiver_public_ip:~
i. exit
j. ssh -i ~/file.pem ubuntu@ receiver_public_ip
k. ls    -->sample.txt should exit 
l. cat sample.txt    --> the text will be same 


3. Mern stack deploy

a.Create instance - ssh and http allow 
                  -network settings -> edit -> add security group -> type : Custom TCP , port range : port no mentioned in env , source type : anywhere 
                  - launch
b.Create folder and open in VS code 
c . in vs code: 
   git clone repo
   if 🔍-> change localhost with  ip
   else file check and change localhost with your public ip

d.for mongodb uri:
   mongodb atlas -> create project(if not created) -> create free cluster -> create db user ->drivers ->get connection string (copy it)
                 -> ur cluster -> left sidebar -> security -> db and n/w access -> n/w access -> add IP -> allow from anywhere (0.0.0.0)
                                                                                ->(if error) db access ->find user(which is in connection string) -> click edit -> set password-> update

e. in env add your connection string (replace <db_password> with your password and add a db name before ?appName)

f. in vs terminal:
   git remote remove origin
   git remote add origin ur repo
   git remote -v
   git add .
   git commit -m "add message"
   git push origin main (git push -u origin main)
   
g.ubuntu terminal (where pem file exist)- 
chmod 400 file.pem
ls -l file.pem 

if error: cp file.pem ~/
          cd ~ 
          then run b 
h. ssh -i ~/file.pem ubuntu@public_ip
i. sudo apt update 
j. go to repo https://github.com/BaviskarMahesh/student-management -> readme.md -> step 4. -> do all the steps mentioned there 
k. browser: http:// public_ip:port no


for salesforce:

1.custom objects:

to create :
⚙️->setup-> quick find -> object manager ->create -> custom object -> enter details 

to check details :
⚙️->setup-> quick find -> object manager -> your object 
                                         -> details you will see there and in fields and relationships (all other objects u need to create)
                                         -> for validation assignments , validation rules (u can see it)
2. apex classes

⚙️->setup-> quick find -> apex classes -> all classes are there and if you want to create click new

3. visualforce pages

⚙️->setup-> quick find -> visualforce pages -> all pages  and for creation - new-> add code , name and label
                                             -> after code is typed / pasted -> click on preview

4. for console based:

no need for 3

⚙️->developer console -> debug -> open execute anonymous windows -> write checking command -> open log(click) -> execute ->debug only

5.for email: no custom objects created

6.for validation :
6.1: if one object

a.create custom objects 
b.add validation rules
c.(if asked: that id is unique)⚙️->setup-> quick find -> object manager -> ur object -> fields and relationships -> id -> edit -> unique
d.setup->tabs->new->custom obj tab->ur object->save
e.setup-> lighting app builder -> new -> app page -> give label -> choose one region -> done
f. drag list view / record form / object home
g. save & activate -> choose app default -> skip and save
h. app launcher(9 dots) -> ur object -> new -> enter data and check

6.2 if two objects :
do 6.1 a,b,c,d,h but do it for two objects -> no need fro e,f and g here 

7.--> for console , the commands:
email:

ConsoleEmailSender.sendEmail(
    'your_email@gmail.com',
    'Console Email Test',
    'This email is sent from Salesforce Apex Console.'
);


for employee management and bank account system :
➕ Option 1: Add Employee
EmployeeManagementSystem.addEmployee(
    101,
    'Rahul Sharma',
    'rahul@example.com',
    Date.newInstance(1995, 5, 15),
    'IT'
);
📋 Option 2: Display Employees
